Key Match Events: Max Fried pitched seven innings of one-run ball, allowing five hits and a walk while striking out eight.
The Atlanta Braves won 3-1 against the Toronto Blue Jays to open their series.
Post-Match Reflections: Max Fried expressed that he has been commanding the ball better and credited his defense for making great plays.
Fried mentioned his goal to give it all he has to get back to the postseason.
Braves catcher Travis d’Arnaud praised Fried for staying calm and executing well.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Braves are tied for the third and final Wild Card spot with the Mets.
The Braves have closed the gap on the Padres and Diamondbacks for the first and second Wild Card spots.
